and would
boost consumption. So, on the
Earned Income

24:23.929 --> 24:26.632 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Tax Credit, there seems to be
common ground.

24:26.665 --> 24:32.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I hope we can find many of those
small-ticket
items which will push the
envelope further

24:32.271 --> 24:34.139 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and increase growth in the U.S.

24:34.173 --> 24:40.579 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And if these
remedies that
you lay out are not enacted,
what's your concern

24:40.612 --> 24:42.381 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for the future of the economy?

24:42.414 --> 24:49.188 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE LAGARDE: You know, if
those issues
such as low participation in the
labor force,

24:49.221 --> 24:58.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
increased poverty, reduced
productivity and
polarization in terms of income
are not addressed,

24:58.230 --> 25:04.269 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
then the U.S. economy will face
what I have
called this new mediocre, where
potential

25:04.303 --> 25:11.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
growth is lower, there is
growth, there is
a degree of recovery, but not
sufficiently

25:11.377 --> 25:18.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to bring people out of those
poverty levels
that we talked about, not enough
to increase

25:18.851 --> 25:23.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the middle class, and not enough
to address
the unemployment of those who
are still looking

25:23.922 --> 25:25.624 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for jobs.

25:25.657 --> 25:30.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But those forces, poverty,
participation,
productivity, and polarization
of income,

25:30.763 --> 25:33.832 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are there to stay unless they
are addressed.

25:33.866 --> 25:36.535 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Finally, a
different question.

25:36.568 --> 25:41.774 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
