been clear. You have made public
statements

25:46.745 --> 25:51.884 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about how you think this, if it
happens, would
be harmful to Great Britain, to
other parts

25:51.917 --> 25:53.719 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the world.

25:53.752 --> 25:57.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How do you see the effect on the
United States
if there is a vote to leave,
Brexit, to leave

25:57.856 --> 25:59.625 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the European Union?

25:59.658 --> 26:03.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE LAGARDE: Well, if the
U.K. decided
to leave the European Union,
there would be

26:03.962 --> 26:10.402 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
some effect on the U.S. economy.
How big that
effect would be, difficult to
say.

26:10.436 --> 26:18.143 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are two channels of
communication of
uncertainty and lack of demand.
One is through

26:18.177 --> 26:24.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
trade, less trade between the
U.S. and the
U.K. most likely. But it's not a
huge volume.

26:24.883 --> 26:28.086 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So that impact would be
relatively low.

26:28.120 --> 26:35.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
However, on the financial front,
because of
the role played by London as a
financial center,

26:35.594 --> 26:43.235 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because of the potential impact
on volatility,
on the anxiety of people who
then sort of

26:43.268 --> 26:50.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
fly to -- fly their money to
safe havens,
then there could be a
significant impact on

26:50.409 --> 26:51.577 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the U.S. economy.

26:51.610 --> 26:53.412 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Americans
should be watching
closely?

26:53.445 --> 26:57.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRISTINE LAGARDE: I think we
should all be
watching closely, yes. And I
hope the right

26:57.549 --> 26:59.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
decision is made, but it's for
the U.K. people
to decide.

