of the LEGO kit.

35:12.577 --> 35:16.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The very fact that we humans are
capable of
creating machines which can be
more capable

35:16.915 --> 35:23.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
than we ever can be, that is
fascinating.
That's just like cheating
evolution.

35:23.822 --> 35:29.194 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Over the years, learned
locomotion, how to
control motors, how to put
things together,

35:29.227 --> 35:30.996 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
how to make robots better.

35:31.029 --> 35:35.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: He learned
to turn toys
into tools. The idea for the
speech device

35:35.533 --> 35:40.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
