38:51.462 --> 38:56.534 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As part of her year-long look at
solutions
to racism, special correspondent
Charlayne

38:56.568 --> 39:02.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hunter-Gault talks with a
teacher on how to
successfully teach in integrated
settings.

39:02.207 --> 39:06.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: The
percentage of
black and Latino students in
what's being

39:06.678 --> 39:12.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
called apartheid schools is on
the increase,
and yet most schools seem
ill-prepared to

39:12.183 --> 39:17.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
help those students be the best
they can be,
while reducing prejudice and
teaching them

39:17.522 --> 39:19.624 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to learn to live with each
other.

39:19.657 --> 39:24.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Maureen Costello of the
Southern Poverty
Law Center says there are ways
to achieve

39:24.295 --> 39:26.164 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
all three.

39:26.197 --> 39:27.832 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Maureen Costello, thank you for
joining us.

39:27.865 --> 39:29.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO, Southern
Poverty Law Center:
Thank you.

39:29.567 --> 39:33.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: The
Southern Poverty
Law Center has a curriculum that
looks at

39:33.771 --> 39:37.308 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
teaching tolerance in schools.
What caused
that to happen?

39:37.342 --> 39:42.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: Well, before
we started
this program, we were fighting
hate crimes,

39:42.680 --> 39:44.515 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
basically.

39:44.549 --> 39:50.021 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Morris Dees, our founder, was
bringing civil
suits against groups like the
Klan, and often

39:50.054 --> 39:59.297 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the young men who had committed
some terrible
acts against others were
motivated by terrible,

39:59.330 --> 40:02.734 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
terrible hatred and just
complete misunderstanding
of what other people were like.

40:02.767 --> 40:04.669 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: It was
mostly race
at that point.

40:04.702 --> 40:08.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: It was usually
race, although,
sometimes, it was also
ethnicity.

40:08.573 --> 40:13.745 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But he was seeing 19- and
20-year-old perpetrators
who were going to spend the rest
of their

40:13.778 --> 40:20.018 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lives in prison. And he said,
you know, we
have to do something to stop
this before it

40:20.051 --> 40:23.288 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
starts. And he said, we need a
school program.

40:23.321 --> 40:28.192 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And that really was the
beginning of teaching
tolerance. Let's find the best
research we

40:28.226 --> 40:33.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
can find about how we can reduce
prejudice
starting at early ages, and
let's get it out

40:33.298 --> 40:35.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
there to teachers.

40:35.066 --> 40:38.403 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the issues in American
education is
that 80 percent of our teachers
are white

40:38.436 --> 40:39.404 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
women.

40:39.437 --> 40:41.172 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: In the
whole country?

40:41.205 --> 40:44.742 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: Yes. And I'm
not saying
white women can't teach, because
I am a white

40:44.776 --> 40:47.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
woman, and I did teach for a
very, very long
time.

40:47.912 --> 40:55.620 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they bring in all of their
own expectations
and beliefs into class. And
teachers have

40:55.653 --> 41:00.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to kind of constantly examine
those and say,
wait a minute, am I making some
judgments

41:00.491 --> 41:02.226 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
here that I shouldn't be making?

41:02.260 --> 41:05.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: How do
you then deal
with such an equation?

41:05.363 --> 41:10.468 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: American
classrooms are
diverse as a whole, but, in
fact, when you

41:10.501 --> 41:15.640 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
get down to individual
classrooms and individual
schools, we see a lot of the
diversity fade

41:15.673 --> 41:17.608 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
away.

41:17.642 --> 41:21.412 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we have schools today that
are more segregated
than they have been in the last
25 years were.

41:21.446 --> 41:23.348 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: This is
even in public
schools?

41:23.381 --> 41:25.883 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: Absolutely,
absolutely.
There's real disparities.

41:25.917 --> 41:28.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: So how
do you get
a handle on that?

41:28.086 --> 41:32.023 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: Every
teacher's job and
the job of school is to help
students develop

41:32.056 --> 41:35.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the skills that they need to
thrive in a diverse
society.

41:35.960 --> 41:42.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Lots of people think it's a
natural thing.
We're all born open-minded, and
then we learn

41:42.400 --> 41:47.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to become bigots. And the fact
is, that's
not necessarily true. You have
to actually

41:47.071 --> 41:52.944 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
develop skills to cross
boundaries. And we
look at it three ways. We say,
OK, first of

41:52.977 --> 41:58.416 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
all, we want to reduce
prejudice, which means
dismantle stereotypes as much as
possible.

41:58.449 --> 42:00.184 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: How do
you do that?

42:00.218 --> 42:05.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: You challenge
them. You
get kids to explore stereotypes
about their

42:05.656 --> 42:11.629 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
own group. And once they
recognize that the
stereotypes of their group are
not really

42:11.662 --> 42:16.734 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
real, you ask them to look at
other stereotypes
in other groups.

42:16.768 --> 42:21.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A stereotype is simply a box.
It's a very
convenient one. It helps us
categorize people.

42:21.939 --> 42:29.013 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're natural categorizers. But
real people
don't all fit in the box. And so
what we have

42:29.046 --> 42:32.650 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to do is help students
understand that there
is no single story.

42:32.683 --> 42:35.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: What do
you do to
break through some of these
problems?

42:35.987 --> 42:38.122 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: We provide
resources for
teachers.

42:38.156 --> 42:42.960 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And one of the main resources is
a curriculum.
So, we have a curriculum called
Perspectives

42:42.994 --> 42:49.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for a Diverse America. And at
its heart are
a series of texts that we have
chosen because

42:49.534 --> 42:52.470 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they're either windows or
mirrors.

42:52.503 --> 42:58.342 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Windows. Windows are how I can
look outside
and I can see experiences and
lives that are

42:58.376 --> 43:02.980 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
different than mine. And that's
something
we have always said is important
in education,

43:03.014 --> 43:06.083 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is to learn about other people
and how other
people live.

43:06.117 --> 43:11.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mirrors are where I can see
myself reflected
in the books that I'm reading.
And, of course,

43:11.722 --> 43:17.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that's important too, and it's
particularly
important for a child of color,
for a child

43:17.462 --> 43:24.101 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who perhaps has immigrant
parents, for children
living in poverty, to recognize
that they're

43:24.135 --> 43:28.172 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not on the outside, that they
can be the heroes
of their own story, too.

43:28.206 --> 43:30.675 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: So where
do they get
those books and that material?

43:30.708 --> 43:34.745 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: We have it in
our Web site,
Perspectives for a Diverse
America. Many of

43:34.779 --> 43:40.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
them are from published works.
And we have
chosen them because they help
teachers explore

43:40.718 --> 43:45.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the issues -- the areas of
identity, diversity,
justice, and action, which we
consider to

43:46.023 --> 43:48.459 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
be really the key parts of
teaching tolerance.

43:48.493 --> 43:53.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Do you
find that teachers
around the country want this
kind of information,

43:53.130 --> 43:54.832 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and how are they responding?

43:54.866 --> 43:59.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAUREEN COSTELLO: The feedback
we're getting
is, we need this. Thank goodness
